        "high_school": {
          "readingText": "Our class recently welcomed an <span class='story-clickable text-blue-600 font-bold border-b-2 border-blue-300 cursor-pointer hover:bg-blue-50 px-1 rounded transition-colors' data-word='exchange student' data-ja='交換留学生'>exchange student</span> from the United States. He appeared genuinely enthusiastic, but a significant <span class='story-clickable text-blue-600 font-bold border-b-2 border-blue-300 cursor-pointer hover:bg-blue-50 px-1 rounded transition-colors' data-word='language barrier' data-ja='言葉の壁'>language barrier</span> immediately emerged. Our classmates tried to engage him with localized Japanese expressions, resulting only in confusion. This led to a misunderstanding, as many students perceived his silence as rudeness or indifference. He quickly became <span class='story-clickable text-blue-600 font-bold border-b-2 border-blue-300 cursor-pointer hover:bg-blue-50 px-1 rounded transition-colors' data-word='isolated' data-ja='孤立した、分離された'>isolated</span> within the classroom environment.",
